result.execSummary:
The defendant Quinn Rf Moebius was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
STRAIGHT TIME.
Apply 52 days credit, if revoked.

Court will allow transfer to Milwaukee County or Ozaukee County.
Concurrent with: any other probation.

miscConds.notes:
Court costs are to be paid as a Condition of Probation.  DNA surcharge is waived.

  If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged/terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collection may include income assignment.
Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling.
AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended.

ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
Submit to random urine screens.
No use or possession of alcohol, illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.
No use or possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
Inform Agent of any and all prescriptions.
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent.
No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged and distributed.
No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (for example, bars, taverns or liquor stores).
No contact with any co-actor listed in the criminal complaint.
Placement at the Salvation Army and follow through with programming.
Compliance with any A.T.R. (alternative to revocation) or D.P.A. (deferred prosecution agreement out of Milwaukee).

supervisions.notes:
STRAIGHT TIME.

Consecutive to: Count 5, if revoked.

Court will allow transfer to Milwaukee County or Ozaukee County.
Concurrent with: any other probation.

miscConds.notes: Court costs are to be paid as a Condition of Probation.
Same conditions for probation apply as to Count 5.
